This package (madmom-infer) is an independent, from-scratch reimplementation of
algorithms published in madmom by the Department of Computational Perception,
Johannes Kepler University, Linz, Austria, and the Austrian Research Institute
for Artificial Intelligence (OFAI), Vienna, Austria. The original madmom
research, algorithm design, and publications remain the work of the original
authors. madmom-infer provides a from-scratch numpy/scipy (with optional
torch) implementation targeting modern Python, without depending on or
redistributing any of madmom's original source code.

Note: this license covers madmom-infer's SOURCE CODE only. madmom's own
pretrained model weights are separately licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0
(non-commercial) by the original authors, and madmom-infer never bundles or
redistributes them -- see NOTICE.

